# Paradigm Shift

Theme adapted for Nikola by [Stéphane Manet](https://github.com/stephmnt) based on the open source template from [HTML5 UP](https://html5up.net).

## Installation

There are two common ways to install the theme.

### Option 1: Install from the Nikola theme index

```shell
    nikola theme -i paradigm-shift
```

Then enable it in your site `conf.py`:

```python
    THEME = "paradigm-shift"
```

### Option 2: Use this repository (local development)

If you have this repository locally, point Nikola to the `v8` theme directory
and enable the theme:

```python
    THEME = "paradigm-shift"
    EXTRA_THEMES_DIRS = ["/path/to/nikola-themes/v8"]
```

Alternatively, copy `v8/paradigm-shift` into your site's `themes/` directory
and set `THEME = "paradigm-shift"` in `conf.py`.

After installation, run `nikola build` (and `nikola serve -b` to preview).

## General settings

The theme uses:

```python
    BLOG_IMAGE_URL
    BLOG_AUTHOR = ""  # (translatable)
    BLOG_BASELINE = "" # (translatable)
    BLOG_EMAIL = ""
    BLOG_DESCRIPTION = ""  # (translatable)
```

## Theme settings

The theme is configured via `THEME_CONFIG` in `conf.py`. These options drive
the intro header (index) and the footer call-to-action block.

Example (multilingual):

```python
    THEME_CONFIG = {
        "fr": {
            "blog_baseline": "Mon portfolio",
            "blog_image_url": "/images/hero.jpg",
            "footer_cta_title": "Restons en contact",
            "footer_cta_text": "Contactez-moi par email ou parcourez mon portfolio",
            "footer_cta_buttons": [
                {"text": "Voir le portfolio", "link": "/posts/portfolio/"},
                {"text": "Me contacter", "link": "mailto:you@example.com"},
            ],
            "social_links": [
                {"name": "LinkedIn", "url": "https://linkedin.com/in/you", "icon": "linkedin"},
                {"name": "GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/you", "icon": "github"},
            ],
        },
        "en": {
            "blog_baseline": "My portfolio",
            "blog_image_url": "/images/hero.jpg",
            "footer_cta_title": "Stay in touch",
            "footer_cta_text": "Email me or browse my portfolio",
            "footer_cta_buttons": [
                {"text": "See my portfolio", "link": "/posts/portfolio/"},
                {"text": "Mail me", "link": "mailto:you@example.com"},
            ],
            "social_links": [
                {"name": "LinkedIn", "url": "https://linkedin.com/in/you", "icon": "linkedin"},
                {"name": "GitHub", "url": "https://github.com/you", "icon": "github"},
            ],
        },
    }
```

If your site is single-language, you can limit `THEME_CONFIG` to
`{DEFAULT_LANG: {...}}`.

### Option details

- `blog_baseline`: title shown in the intro header (home page).
- `blog_image_url`: image shown in the intro header (used directly in `src`).
- `footer_cta_title`: title of the footer call-to-action block.
- `footer_cta_text`: text of the call-to-action block (optional).
- `footer_cta_buttons`: list of buttons `{text, link}`; the first is styled as primary.
- `social_links`: list of links `{name, url, icon}` rendered as icons.
  `icon` matches a Font Awesome Brands name (e.g., `github`, `linkedin`).
